                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The gorgon breathes a 60-foot cone of green gas. Each creature in the area must attempt a <span data-pf2-check=\"fortitude\" data-pf2-dc=\"25\" data-pf2-traits=\"earth,incapacitation,primal,transmutation\" data-pf2-label=\"Breath Weapon DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Fortitude</span> save.</p>\n<p>The gorgon can't use Breath Weapon again for [[/r 1d4 #rounds]] rounds.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature's body hardens and stiffens, causing it to become @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Slowed]{Slowed 1} for 1 round.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature becomes @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Petrified]{Petrified} for 1 minute. It can attempt a new save at the end of each of its turns.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature becomes petrified permanently.</p>"
